                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratori</ex></expan> Caesa</supplied>ri <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> et civitati ita <supplied reason="lost">iubente</supplied> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">senat</supplied>u ut promiserat <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> Arm<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">niu</supplied>s Tauriscus pontem fecit </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <supplied reason="lost">Αὐτοκρ</supplied>άτορι Καίσαρι καὶ τῇ πόλει <supplied reason="lost">Τ(ίτος) Ἀρμίνι</supplied><lb break="no" n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">ος Ταυ</supplied>ρίσκος ἐπόησε τὴν γέφυραν καθὼς <supplied reason="lost">ἐπηγ</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">γείλατο κ</supplied>ατὰ τὸ δόγμα τῶν συνέδρων ἐφ’ ᾧ<supplied reason="lost">τε</supplied> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">λήψεσθ</supplied>αι αὐτὸν τὸ ἐπινόμιον καὶ βαλάνω<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">ὅσων</supplied> ἔχει θρεμμάτων διὰ βίου
            </ab></div></div>
